		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Legalizing Recreational Drugs
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1849276">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The thing every side against legalization misses is very simple.<br />
<br />
The drug abusers are not in power. The drug suppliers are. Making them illegal makes them more poweful. By treating illegal drug abusers, the enforcers pay both sides: their containment, and their persecution. That's double.<br />
<br />
By legalizing them, the government can create some semblance of profit via taxation for the exact product that is being served and processed against, potentially reduce the amount of illegal and incorrect development of numerous intravenous drug cocktails and the like, take profit away from cartels, reduce related drug traffic deaths and the like, and take power from the drug trade that is coming into the United states.<br />
<br />
Illegal, governmental pays for treatment and enforcement. LEGAL, government gets money for treatment and pays less for enforcement.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
