			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Legalizing Recreational Drugs
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1849319">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Tinthalas Tigris</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=010f2ed7a4faafe15dd3307f0d227507&amp;p=1849308#post1849308" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Oh hell yes they are. Have you not heard the phrase, &quot;first is free?&quot;</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Yes.  It's manipulative, it's marketing, but it's not coercion.  It doesn't work on someone who isn't already open to the idea.<br />
<br />
More importantly, suppliers and dealers appear based on an individual assessment of risk vs reward.  Drug dealers choose to assume a great deal of risk (death, jail) for substantial rewards (money and power).  Knocking off dealers just increases the &quot;reward&quot; side of the equation for remaining dealers.  And if you manage to knock them all out, the reward proposition skyrockets until there's a man bold enough to assume the risks.  This increasingly selects for the most ruthless, corrupt, and dangerous kind of people.  So while fighting the dealers may help shrink the market somewhat by driving up prices, it's not as good a solution as thwarting the demand at the source: the users themselves.<br />
<br />
In the strictly economic sense, dealers do not have much meaningful control over the abusers.  They have some ability to stimulate demand and may exert all manner of incidental control over specific situations but broadly speaking, the dealers are salesman and users are their customers.  Salesman are always dependent on customers.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
